HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1579
By Harris
A RESOLUTION to commend Taylor Sinclair for her service as a
legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this body is pleased to recognize certain persons
who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, Taylor Sinclair is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her
role as a legislative intern for Representative Torrey C. Harris; Ms. Sinclair's work has resulted
in innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole;
and
WHEREAS, a student at Tennessee State University, where she is highly regarded by
her peers, Ms. Sinclair is majoring in criminal justice and has compiled an impressive academic
record as a consistent member of the Dean's List; she is also currently completing her capstone
project on racial disparity; and
WHEREAS, demonstrating her commitment to campus involvement, Taylor Sinclair was
the sergeant at arms of Sigma Alpha Iota and is a member of Tennessee State University's
Grammy award-winning marching band, Aristocrat of Bands, and the wind ensemble; and
WHEREAS, after graduating in May 2026, Ms. Sinclair aspires to work in the legal and
policy field; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Taylor Sinclair brought her many
abilities and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred
Fourteenth General Assembly; and
HJR1579
018259
- 1 -

WHEREAS, during her tenure as a legislative intern, she has risen to every challenge
presented to her, going above and beyond in the performance of her duties; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Sinclair has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Taylor Sinclair for outstanding service as a legislative
intern for Representative Torrey C. Harris and extend to her our best wishes for every future
success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
